  "stem": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The cost to rent a commercial fishing boat from a certain company is <math alttext=\"dollar sign 950\"><mo>$</mo><mn>950</mn></math> for the first <math alttext=\"2\"><mn>2</mn>\n</math> hours and an additional <math alttext=\"dollar sign 50\"><mo>$</mo><mn>50</mn></math> per hour for each hour after the first <math alttext=\"2\"><mn>2</mn>\n</math> hours. If the total cost to rent the commercial fishing boat from the company for <math alttext=\"t\"><mi>t</mi>\n</math> hours, where <math alttext=\"t greater than 2\"><mi>t</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><mn>2</mn></math>, is <math alttext=\"dollar sign 1,100\"><mo>$</mo><mn>1,100</mn></math>, which equation represents this situation?</p>",
